<br>
I am posting this here because in the past I have found little information on this quest. Hopefully this will make it into the Tomes of Knowledge.<br>
<br>
Greydon Moondancer<br>
Erudite Paladin of Quellious<br>
the Nameless<br>
<br>
Originally written early 2000... last update... Sept 2000.<br>
<br>
I just did this quest the other day. I have the scoop on all the information after much painstaking effort...<br>
<br>
whew...<br>
<br>
There are several quests which all intersect with each other, so although some of the items listed below are used in this multi-tier quest, they may also be used for other quests:<br>
<br>
Bayle List II<br>
Order of Thunder Badge<br>
Thunder Staff<br>
Bonethunder Staff<br>
<br>
My focus here is on the Quest for the Bonethunder Staff, which involves all the items listed above. I will make note of other quests with regard to those items, but only for those of which I know.<br>
<br>
This quest begins in South Qeynos with Runethar Hamest. He can be found within the Temple of Thunder, a cleric/paladin guild located behind the Fish's Ale. Runethar needs the Bayle List II and the Thunder Staff for which he will give you the Bonethunder Staff. Please note that this will require very good standing with the Knights of Thunder faction. Even with a standing of warmly, Runethar still would not tell me about the quest. I had to start over from the begining to find this out. However, based on Runthar's responses when I attempted<br>
to give him the final items, I knew I had the right ones.<br>
<br>
Please note the following item drops:<br>
<br>
Mammoth Bear drops Bayle List II<br>
Drosco the zombie drops Order of Thunder<br>
Wolten Grafe drops Thunder Staff<br>
Runethar Hamest drops Bonethunder Staff<br>
<br>
Runthar Hamest is a Paladin in the Temple of Thunder, South Qeynos<br>
Wolten Grafe is a Paladin in the Temple of Thunder, South Qeynos<br>
<br>
Order of Thunder given to Wolten = Thunder Staff<br>
Bayle List II plus Thunder Staff given to Runethar = Bonethunder STaff<br>
<br>
<br>
Steps are as follows:<br>
<br>
1. Go to Surefall Glade and enter the bear caves. Inside the caves you'll eventually find the<br>
Mammoth Bear (around lvl 20). He spawns about every 2 hours behind the waterfall. He will wander the caves, stopping by the large inner pool and by the crossroads, all inside the caves. If you kill the bear, he will drop a Hi Quality Bear Hide and the Bayle List II.<br>
<br>
The Bayle List II can be obtained without killing the bear. This involves Nitrates obtained from the Druids in Surefall and then going to Ak'Anon, the gnome city. This is part of another long term quest involving several Bayle Lists.<br>
<br>
The Hi Q Bear Hide may be given to Frenway Marthank in the Jagged Pine building for faction and exp. Or you may sell it to a player.<br>
<br>
2. Go inside the Qeynos Catacombs and find Drosco the zombie. This is where much confusion lay with many people. Drosco used to be a named zombie, however sometime early this year (2000), his label was changed to "a zombie". Having spent much time in the catacombs doing this quest, I can assure you this is the only zombie that wanders there. He spawns about every 20 - 25 minutes, sometimes being replaced by a gelatinous cube. He spawns at approx loc of 415, neg 20 which is inside the corridor just before the large hexagonal rooms before the skeleton alcoves. This loc is in a turn of the corridor.<br>
<br>
Editors note: Qeynos Catacombs have undergone changes since this was quest completed and documented. It is much harder now to camp Drosco at his spawn point.<br>
<br>
From Drosco, you will obtain the Order of Thunder Badge. It looks like a necklace, is Magic and NO DROP. This is important to note. There are tradeable/sellable Order Of Thunder Badges you can get in the Karanas, but those will not work for this quest. Wolten will not accept any but the one dropped by Drosco. I have tested this myself as I came upon an Order of Thunder Badge in the Karanas, but they would not work.<br>
<br>
Drosco drops a few items, some of which are rare drops, so it may take a few attempts before you find the Order of Thunder. Among the tiems dropped are: A Sealed Note (Letter), Order of Thunder, and a Misc item, such as a rusty weapon.<br>
<br>
The note can be used with Wolten Grafe to begin another quest that takes you to Freeport.<br>
The Order of Thunder, including those from the Karanas, can be used with a female paladin (name unavailable at this time) in the same temple. She gives faction, exp, and an item in return.<br>
<br>
Please note that Drosco is also part of a quest for the Temple of Bertox which is in the sewers.<br>
<br>
<br>
3. Return the Order of Thunder Badge to Wolten Grafe at the Temple of Thunder for the Thunder Staff.<br>
<br>
4. Give the Thunder Staff and Bayle List II to Runethar Hamest for the Bonethunder Staff.<br>
<br>
Congrats, you now have:<br>
<br>
Bonethunder Staff<br>
Damage: 9<br>
Delay: 36 <br>
Ratio: 4 Average <br>
Wis: +3  <br>
Weight: 10.0 <br>
Weapon Skill: Two Hand Blunt <br>
Classes: Cleric Paladin  <br>
Races: All Races  <br>
Inventory Slot: Primary Melee <br>
Can be stored in Medium and larger containers <br>
